<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 92 / Firebombs in MetroCentre
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SIX incendiary devices ignited early today in the Gateshead MetroCentre,
Europe's largest shopping complex. Three others were found and made safe by
bomb disposal officers. The police said the fires had caused minimal damage
to stores and that no one had been hurt.
'These were professional devices,' Mr David Mellish, assistant chief
constable for Northumbria. 'They would have caused serious fire damage and
could have resulted in serious loss of life had they gone off this afternoon
when the centre was crowded.'
The centre was evacuated when two firebombs were discovered, and fires
caused by other devices broke out as police were searching premises.
No warnings were given, and police were unable to say when the devices were
planted or who was responsible. The incendiaries, which contained timing
devices, were thought to be similar to devices planted in shopping centres
at Blackpool, Manchester and north London in December.
</TEXT>
