<TEXT>
SHARES in Pinelands, a New Jersey-based company, soared Dollars 5 7/8 to
Dollars 17 7/8 in active trading on Wall Street yesterday on news that the
company had agreed to be acquired by Chris-Craft Industries for Dollars 18 a
share or about Dollars 310m, writes Karen Zagor in New York.
If the deal goes ahead, it will allow Chris-Craft to become one of the
largest US non-network television station businesses by giving the group a
foothold in the important New York market. Chris-Craft's BHC Communications
division operates seven stations.
On Wall Street, shares in Chris-Craft slipped Dollars  3/4 to Dollars 26 3/4
.
