<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAY 92 / Finance &amp; The Family: Directors' Transactions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS MACDONALD, Directus Ltd
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DIRECTORS' dealing activity has now calmed down to a more reasoned level
where the overall picture is no longer distorted by one-off influences.
Clinton Cards retails greeting cards and gifts throughout England. Directors
have been buying shares during April. Most recently Clinton Lewin, the
managing director, and Don Lewin, the chairman, both bought 25,000 shares at
76p. That is 16p higher than the price at which three directors bought two
weeks earlier.
Selling at Renishaw, the metrology and inspection equipment company, has
been a feature since the end of last year. Most recently Allan Roberts, the
finance director, sold 24,000 shares at 272p.
John Hall, the deputy chairman of Hall Engineering, and Robert McAlpine, a
non-executive director, both purchased shares in this steel processing
group.
Hall bought 14,000 shares at 152p in an off-market deal on April 29, while
McAlpine paid 148.5p for 15,000 shares from the market on April 23.
Results were announced at the beginning of April and the chairman said that
the board was confident about future prospects.
