<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAY 92 / Markets (At a glance): Yield curve flattens
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The cut in base rates this week further narrowed the gap between short and
long term interest rates (the yield on long-dated gilts). For a long time,
it was standard for short term rates to be below long term - in the jargon,
a positive yield curve - but in recent times a negative yield curve has been
the norm. Forcing short term rates any lower will probably require a similar
move in Germany.
