FT  09 MAY 92 / Banda faces crisis
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JOHANNESBURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
At least thirty-seven people were killed this week in Malawi's worst civil
unrest, Reuter reports from Johannesburg. There have been four days of
strikes, presenting President Hastings Banda with the worst crisis of his
28-year rule.
