<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAY 92 / International Company News: Hughes may buy General Dynamics
missiles unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HUGHES Aircraft, the aerospace subsidiary of General Motors, is negotiating
to buy the missiles operations of General Dynamics, the large US defence
contractor, writes Martin Dickson in New York.
General Motors confirmed the discussions yesterday, 24 hours after General
Dynamics told its annual meeting it planned to sell off the business and a
deal could be close.
Raytheon, another large US missiles manufacturer, has also acknowledged
holding discussions with General Dynamics, but added that General Dynamics
was currently negotiating 'with another party'.
Hughes makes tactical guided missiles. General Dynamics' missiles division,
with annual sales of around Dollars 1.3bn, makes tactical products.
</TEXT>
